Description.
Protoconch multispiral (about 1.75 whorls), planispiral, smooth (
Fig. 7A
), transition to teleoconch I marked by apertural varix (
Fig. 7A
). Teleoconch I short, sculptured with weak axial threads, crossed by irregular longitudinal sculpture, creating a reticular pattern (
Fig. 7B
), transition to teleoconch II marked by slight axial constriction followed by change in sculpture (
Figs. 7A, D, G
). Teleoconch II about the same length of teleoconch I, sculptured with irregular longitudinal sculpture, crossed by low axial annuli (
Fig. 7C
), transition to teleoconch III marked by change in sculpture (
Fig. 7D
). Teleoconch III sculptured with axial annuli, crossed by short longitudinal striae (
Fig. 7E
), transition to teleoconch IV marked by change in sculpture (
Figs. 7D, G
). Teleoconch IV sculptured with axial ribs, longitudinal striae within interspaces only (
Fig. 7F
), transition to teleoconch V marked by suture, immediately followed by pronounced axial ribs (
Figs. 7D, G
). Teleoconch V (last growth stage) average size for genus [Tol 
2.10–2.56 mm
], tubular, thick, robust, moderately and regularly arched [Larc: 
0.62–0.77 mm
; Arc: 
0.20–0.28 mm
], subcylindrical with increase in diameter from posterior to aperture, cream with brownish mottling (
Figs. 6
A–B). Surface sculptured with axial ribs and longitudinal striae within the interspaces (
Figs. 7
H–I). Striae thin, but dense (
Fig. 7H
). Axial sculpture comprising of 24–34 raised, strong, narrow to wide, quadrangular ribs, rather closely arranged and regularly spaced (
Fig. 7I
), except last 3–4 preceding aperture, which are slightly larger (
Figs. 6
A–B, F; 7I). Axial interspaces moderately deep, narrower than ribs (
Fig. 7I
), except last rib preceding apertural ribs, which is somewhat wider (
Fig. 7I
). Posterior [Dpe: 
0.45–0.53 mm
] with thick edge, squared shoulder (
Fig. 7I
). Septum mucronate (
Fig. 7I
). Mucro with low rounded point, positioned along dorsal margin (
Fig. 7I
). Aperture [Da: 
0.59–0.70 mm
] with 3–4 large axial ribs, last one to two sharply reduced in width on ventral side (
Fig. 7I
). No varix. Lip smooth, with deflected peristome (
Fig. 6C
). Periostracum not observed. Operculum thin, light brown; exterior surface with 6–8 concentric rings (
Figs. 6
D–E). Conceptual reconstruction of growth stages shown in 
Fig. 8A
.
